  "prompt": "My iPhone screen broke I have iCloud, would notifications I received transfer over to a replacement or would contacts transfer and notifications gone?",
  "response": "When you replace or restore your iPhone and use iCloud for backup, here\u2019s what happens with your data:\n\n### **Contacts**\n- **Yes**, your contacts will transfer over to the replacement iPhone as long as they were synced to iCloud. iCloud automatically backs up and syncs your contacts if you have Contacts enabled in your iCloud settings.\n\n### **Notifications**\n- **No**, notifications you received on your old iPhone will not transfer to the replacement. Notifications are temporary and are not stored in iCloud backups. Once dismissed, they are gone unless the app itself stores them (e.g., messaging apps like WhatsApp or email apps that archive notifications).\n\n### **What iCloud Backs Up**\niCloud backs up things like:\n- App data (if the app supports iCloud backup)\n- Photos and videos (if iCloud Photos is enabled)\n- Settings, messages, and call history\n- Health data (if enabled in iCloud settings)\n- Wi-Fi passwords and home screen layout\n\n### **Steps to Restore Data to Your Replacement iPhone**\n1. During setup, select \"Restore from iCloud Backup.\"\n2. Sign in to your iCloud account.\n3. Choose the most recent backup to restore your data.\n\n### **What You\u2019ll Lose**\n- **Notifications**: As mentioned, these are temporary and will not transfer.\n- **Unsynced Data**: Anything not backed up to iCloud (e.g., files in apps that don\u2019t use iCloud backup, or unsaved changes).\n\n### **Tip**\nTo avoid losing important information, regularly check your iCloud backup settings to ensure all critical data is being backed up. If you need to recover notifications, some apps like Messages or Email may store them within the app itself, so check there.\n\nLet me know if you have more questions! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
